</div></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Weeks 1-2 Introduction to the course, Unit 1. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to early language learning.</p>
<p>Weeks 3-4 Unit 2. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to food/consumerism.</p>
<p>Weeks 5-6 Unit 3. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to sport/wellness.</p>
<p>Weeks 7-8 Unit 4. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to life skills/trend.</p>
<p>Weeks 9-10 Unit 5. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to public health/ecology.</p>
<p>Weeks 11-12 Unit 6. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to health/lifestyle.</p>
<p>Weeks 13-14 Unit 7. Students will be able to recognize expressions related to global warming/environment.</p>
<p>Weeks 15-16 Test, writing a paragraph, and review</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Activities in class 30%</p>
<p>Assignments 35%</p>
<p>Review test 35%</p>
<p>Further details will be explained during the first class.</p>
<p><span style="color: #222222; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: #ffffff; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"> </span></p>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>The teacher will explain the grading system in class.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">事前学修：教科書や教材の予習，予習課題に取り組む。</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9"> </span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">（</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">120 </span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">分）</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW188092596 BCX9" data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1}"> </span></p>
<div class="OutlineElement Ltr  BCX9 SCXW188092596">
<p class="Paragraph SCXW188092596 BCX9"><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">事後学修：授業内の講義や解説を理解し</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">，</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">事後課題（レポート，プレゼンテーション，小テストなど）に取り組む。（</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">120</span></span><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">分）</span></span></p>
<p class="Paragraph SCXW188092596 BCX9"><span class="TextRun Highlight SCXW188092596 BCX9" lang="JA-JP" xml:lang="JA-JP" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW188092596 BCX9">Students will be expected to participate actively in class and on the discussion boards. Students will also keep vocabulary notebooks and read extensively.</span></span></p>
